article_title: Doctors See More Paying Patients In States That Expanded Medicaid

article_metadata.description: About one in five patient primary care visits to doctors’ offices are covered by Medicaid in states that expanded the health insurance program for poor Americans under the Affordable Care Act, according to a new analysis.
